   <taskbody>
      <steps class="- topic/ol task/steps ">
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Before starting the work instruction activity, perform the following steps:</cmd>
            <substeps id="substeps_zd4_klw_wcc" class="- topic/ol task/substeps ">
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Do not begin these tasks without confirmation that personnel directly
                     involved have completed the required training associated with the work
                     instruction activity and have reviewed this document.</cmd>
               </substep>
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Gather necessary tools and equipment as identified below in the Equipment
                     Section.</cmd>
               </substep>
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Wear and use additional Personal Protective Equipment (PPE) and safety
                     equipment required for this specific work instruction.</cmd>
               </substep>
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Obey all applicable safety requirements and procedures.</cmd>
               </substep>
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Notify appropriate personnel of the activity and estimated time needed to
                     complete the tasks.</cmd>
               </substep>
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Clearly identify, mark-off, and secure the designated area defined by the
                     work instruction activity.</cmd>
               </substep>
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Follow all Lockout/Tagout procedures when work instruction activity requires
                     isolating energy in the designated area. Verify energy is isolated before
                     starting work.</cmd>
               </substep>
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">After verifying that energy is isolated, remove the protective guarding and
                     open the safety interlock gates.</cmd>
               </substep>
            </substeps>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Prerequisites:</cmd>
            <substeps id="substeps_cvq_5mw_wcc" class="- topic/ol task/substeps ">
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Obtain a sample container with a known height and inner diameter value
                     measured and approved by the quality team.</cmd>
               </substep>
            </substeps>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">To set up the PLUG V5 inspection, perform the following steps:</cmd>
            <substeps id="substeps_xth_hnw_wcc" class="- topic/ol task/substeps ">
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">
                     <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Preliminary Checks</b> Verify the correct calibration of the motor –
                     driven movable frame.</cmd>
                  <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
                     <ol id="ol_hbl_3nw_wcc" class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">Move the movable frame upwards.</li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">Enter the values of the container dimensions (diameter, height).</li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">Move the movable frame downwards.</li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">Use a measuring ruler to check that the height value matches the height
                           parameter entered.  </li>
                     </ol>
                     <p class="- topic/p ">
                        <fig id="fig_j4l_jnw_wcc" class="- topic/fig ">
                           <image href="media/image1.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_k4l_jnw_wcc"
                                  align="center"
                                  class="- topic/image "/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                     <p class="- topic/p ">
                        <fig id="fig_l4l_jnw_wcc" class="- topic/fig ">
                           <image href="media/image2.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_m4l_jnw_wcc"
                                  align="center"
                                  class="- topic/image "/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </info>
               </substep>
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Check the length of the Plug Caliber against the parameter value
                     entered.</cmd>
                  <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
                     <ol id="ol_yvh_pnw_wcc" class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">Go to the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Article</uicontrol> menu <image href="media/image3.jpg"
                                  id="image_d5c_qnw_wcc"
                                  placement="inline"
                                  class="- topic/image "/>,
                              <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Handling</uicontrol>
                           <image href="media/image4.jpg"
                                  id="image_e5c_qnw_wcc"
                                  placement="inline"
                                  class="- topic/image "/>,
                              <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Tooling height</uicontrol>.</li>
                     </ol>
                     <p class="- topic/p ">
                        <fig id="fig_vkd_4dx_wcc" class="- topic/fig ">
                           <image href="media/image5.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_wkd_4dx_wcc"
                                  align="center"
                                  class="- topic/image "/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                     <p class="- topic/p ">
                        <fig id="fig_zmx_4dx_wcc" class="- topic/fig ">
                           <image href="media/image6.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_anx_4dx_wcc"
                                  align="center"
                                  class="- topic/image "/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </info>
               </substep>
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">In Manual mode, bring an article to the station where the PLUG detector is
                     installed (typically station 1).</cmd>
                  <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">
                        <fig id="fig_ztv_12x_wcc" class="- topic/fig ">
                           <image href="media/image7.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_a5v_12x_wcc"
                                  align="center"
                                  class="- topic/image "/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </info>
               </substep>
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">The internal PLUG caliber should be barely out of the external caliber.</cmd>
                  <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
                     <ol id="ol_vly_22x_wcc" class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">The distance between the article and the extractor pipe should be
                           approximately 5mm.</li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">If this distance is not correct, verify the height at the Article file
                           menu.</li>
                     </ol>
                     <p class="- topic/p ">
                        <fig id="fig_u5d_g2x_wcc" class="- topic/fig ">
                           <image href="media/image8.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_v5d_g2x_wcc"
                                  align="center"
                                  class="- topic/image "/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </info>
               </substep>
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">
                     <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Adjust the PLUG Location</b> Adjust the radial PLUG position.</cmd>
                  <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
                     <ol id="ol_lbh_j2x_wcc" class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">Unlock the locking lever [1].</li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">Move the PLUG head radially to center it with the center of the
                           article’s finish.</li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">Lock the locking lever [1]. </li>
                     </ol>
                     <p class="- topic/p ">
                        <fig id="fig_h3v_k2x_wcc" class="- topic/fig ">
                           <image href="media/image9.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_i3v_k2x_wcc"
                                  align="center"
                                  class="- topic/image "/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </info>
               </substep>
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Adjust the centering of the PLUG.</cmd>
                  <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
                     <ol id="ol_u4g_42x_wcc" class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">Unlock the locking lever [1].</li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">Lose the centering screw [2] using a 13mm spanner.</li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">Lock the locking lever [1]. </li>
                     </ol>
                     <p class="- topic/p ">
                        <fig id="fig_ajm_p2x_wcc" class="- topic/fig ">
                           <image href="media/image10.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_bjm_p2x_wcc"
                                  align="center"
                                  class="- topic/image "/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </info>
               </substep>
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Verify that the PLUG caliber is aligned with the article by moving the
                     caliber in Manual mode. Ensure the internal gauge is aligned and does not
                     contact the article.</cmd>
               </substep>
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Check the verticality of the PLUG when all handles are locked.</cmd>
                  <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
                     <ol id="ol_hkk_s2x_wcc" class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">If the verticality is not correct, use the 4 screws around the cylinder
                           block to correct.</li>
                     </ol>
                     <p class="- topic/p ">
                        <fig id="fig_wkp_t2x_wcc" class="- topic/fig ">
                           <image href="media/image11.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_xkp_t2x_wcc"
                                  align="center"
                                  class="- topic/image "/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </info>
               </substep>
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">
                     <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Sensitivity Adjustment</b> To obtain proper inspection, there must be a
                     3mm pressure on the article to make the measurement.</cmd>
                  <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
                     <ol id="ol_zqc_x2x_wcc" class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">Put a 3mm key on the external system to simulate the 3mm pressure on the
                           article.</li>
                     </ol>
                     <p class="- topic/p ">
                        <fig id="fig_syy_x2x_wcc" class="- topic/fig ">
                           <image href="media/image12.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_tyy_x2x_wcc"
                                  align="center"
                                  class="- topic/image "/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </info>
               </substep>
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Unlock the optical barrier at the back. The goal is to put the optical
                     barrier at the limit of the sensor activation.</cmd>
                  <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
                     <ol id="ol_tgy_z2x_wcc" class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">To do this, you must check the light of the optical barrier.</li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">When it is done, check the non-activation of the barrier when you
                           manually put the shuttle up and down without the 3mm key.</li>
                     </ol>
                     <p class="- topic/p ">
                        <fig id="fig_ajx_bfx_wcc" class="- topic/fig ">
                           <image href="media/image13.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_bjx_bfx_wcc"
                                  align="center"
                                  class="- topic/image "/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                     <p class="- topic/p ">
                        <fig id="fig_qkq_cfx_wcc" class="- topic/fig ">
                           <image href="media/image14.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_rkq_cfx_wcc"
                                  align="center"
                                  class="- topic/image "/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </info>
               </substep>
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">
                     <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Sensitivity of internal diameter’s sensor</b> Simulate the 3mm pressure on
                     the article. The goal is to be at the limit of the optical barrier’s sensor
                     activation.</cmd>
                  <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
                     <ol id="ol_gwz_2fx_wcc" class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">Manually run the machine to get the internal gauge 3mm out of its
                           metallic ejector.</li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">Press the internal gauge to simulate the 3mm pressure.</li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">Check the light of the top optical sensor. If the limit sensor does not
                           activate, it must be adjusted.</li>
                     </ol>
                     <p class="- topic/p ">
                        <fig id="fig_ww5_gfx_wcc" class="- topic/fig ">
                           <image href="media/image15.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_xw5_gfx_wcc"
                                  align="center"
                                  class="- topic/image "/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                     <p class="- topic/p ">
                        <fig id="fig_jdk_vgx_wcc" class="- topic/fig ">
                           <image href="media/image16.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_kdk_vgx_wcc"
                                  align="center"
                                  class="- topic/image "/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </info>
               </substep>
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">
                     <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">External Gauge Adjustment</b> In Manual mode:</cmd>
                  <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
                     <ol id="ol_xck_ygx_wcc" class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">Go to <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Configuration</uicontrol>
                           <image href="media/image17.jpg"
                                  id="image_gq1_1hx_wcc"
                                  placement="inline"
                                  class="- topic/image "/>,
                              <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Detector Presence</uicontrol>
                           <image href="media/image18.jpg"
                                  id="image_hq1_1hx_wcc"
                                  placement="inline"
                                  class="- topic/image "/>.</li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">Select the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">PLUG</uicontrol> symbol <image href="media/image19.jpg"
                                  id="image_g14_chx_wcc"
                                  placement="inline"
                                  class="- topic/image "/> under the station
                           where it is installed.</li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">The value for the Plug wedge must be around 155. </li>
                     </ol>
                     <p class="- topic/p ">
                        <fig id="fig_d4y_dhx_wcc" class="- topic/fig ">
                           <image href="media/image20.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_e4y_dhx_wcc"
                                  align="center"
                                  class="- topic/image "/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </info>
               </substep>
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Click on the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Detections/PLUG</b> button to display the PLUG Setup
                     screen.</cmd>
                  <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
                     <ol id="ol_tm4_phx_wcc" class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">
                              <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Activate</uicontrol> or
                              <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">deactivate</uicontrol>
                           </b> the corresponding internal and
                           external inspections (Green = activated, gray = deactivated).  </li>
                     </ol>
                     <p class="- topic/p ">
                        <fig id="fig_yjx_phx_wcc" class="- topic/fig ">
                           <image href="media/image21.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_zjx_phx_wcc"
                                  align="center"
                                  class="- topic/image "/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </info>
               </substep>
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">
                     <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Adjust the external caliber</b> In Production mode.</cmd>
                  <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
                     <ol id="ol_klb_13x_wcc" class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">Pass a good article through the MX4 (example article height =
                           190mm).</li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">Verify that the value given by the external gauge is equal to the real
                           article height.</li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">If the value is correct, click
                              <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Settings</uicontrol>/<uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Apply</uicontrol>.</li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">If the difference between the measured and real height is more than 1mm,
                           modify the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Plug wedge </b>(Step 12).</li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">If the difference is less than 1mm, use the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Offset
                              measure</uicontrol> to correct the measurement.</li>
                     </ol>
                     <p class="- topic/p ">
                        <fig id="fig_wc1_d3x_wcc" class="- topic/fig ">
                           <image href="media/image22.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_xc1_d3x_wcc"
                                  align="center"
                                  class="- topic/image "/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                     <p class="- topic/p ">
                        <fig id="fig_yc1_d3x_wcc" class="- topic/fig ">
                           <image href="media/image23.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_zc1_d3x_wcc"
                                  align="center"
                                  class="- topic/image "/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </info>
               </substep>
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Adjust the height threshold values.</cmd>
                  <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
                     <ol id="ol_hsr_33x_wcc" class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">The external peak indicates the moment when the external caliber makes
                           contact with the container. </li>
                     </ol>
                     <p class="- topic/p ">
                        <fig id="fig_msv_33x_wcc" class="- topic/fig ">
                           <image href="media/image24.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_nsv_33x_wcc"
                                  align="center"
                                  class="- topic/image "/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </info>
               </substep>
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">
                     <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Internal Gauge Adjustment</b> In Manual mode:</cmd>
                  <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
                     <ol id="ol_bfg_m3x_wcc" class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">Pass a good article through the PLUG station.</li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">Verify that the value given by the internal gauge is equal to the real
                           article height.</li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">If the value is correct, click
                              <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Settings</uicontrol>/<uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Apply</uicontrol>.</li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">If the difference is less than 1mm, use the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Offset measure</b> to
                           correct the measurement. </li>
                     </ol>
                     <p class="- topic/p ">
                        <fig id="fig_l4d_mmx_wcc" class="- topic/fig ">
                           <image href="media/image25.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_m4d_mmx_wcc"
                                  align="center"
                                  class="- topic/image "/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </info>
               </substep>
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">If the difference between the measured and real height is more than
                     1mm:</cmd>
                  <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
                     <ol id="ol_rxk_4mx_wcc" class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">Slowly move down the external caliber until the optical barrier is
                           activated (LED [1] will turn off).</li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">Unlock the nut [2] located on the internal axes.</li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">Untighten or loosen the nut [3] to have more or less compression on the
                           internal caliber. </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">Find the correct position to turn off the LED [4] of the optical
                           internal barrier.</li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">Lock the system using the nut [2].</li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">Verify the new measured value.  </li>
                     </ol>
                     <p class="- topic/p ">
                        <fig id="fig_yrd_qmx_wcc" class="- topic/fig ">
                           <image href="media/image26.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_zrd_qmx_wcc"
                                  align="center"
                                  class="- topic/image "/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                     <p class="- topic/p ">
                        <fig id="fig_asd_qmx_wcc" class="- topic/fig ">
                           <image href="media/image27.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_bsd_qmx_wcc"
                                  align="center"
                                  class="- topic/image "/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </info>
               </substep>
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Adjust the height threshold values.</cmd>
                  <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
                     <ol id="ol_lgf_tmx_wcc" class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">The internal peak indicates the moment when the external caliber makes
                           contact with the container.</li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">When passing a good article, both internal and external peaks should be
                           aligned as shown. </li>
                     </ol>
                     <p class="- topic/p ">
